						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of a slab standing near the Siddharāmēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1033.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 955, Śrīmukha, ba. 2, Wednesday, Visākhānakshatra.</hi> The name of the month is not given. The intended date seems to be <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1033, March 21, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is broken away after the date portion.</p>						

						</summary>
